Package info.kgeorgiy.ja.treshchev.implementor

Class Implementor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.treshchev.implementor.Implementor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Impler, JarImpler
public class Implementor
extends Object
implements JarImpler
Class implementing JarImpler interface. Provides public methods to create .java and .jar file that implements given interface. Note that this class expects exactly the interface for implementation.

For example, if the given interface is located in package info.kgeorgiy.ja.treshchev.implementor than Package-path to created .java file has a value different from the package name by replacement "." on File.separatorChar.

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main​(String[] args)
      Main function. Provides to user the console to run Implementor class. Runs in two variants:
      1. if there were 2 arguments token outputPath of command line than it creates .java file in outputPath directory containing the implementation of the interface token using implement(Class, Path) method.
      2. if there were 3 arguments -jar token jarFile of command line than it creates .jar file on the jarFile path where located compiled .java file containing the implementation of the interface token using implementJar(Class, Path) method.
      If there were some errors during the operation of the method than there would be an error message in System.err stream. If there were less than 2 or more than 3 arguments, or there were 3 arguments and the first argument wasn't -jar, than method will print corresponding error message in System.err stream.
      Parameters:
      args - command line arguments for the app.

    • implement

      public void implement​(Class<?> clazz, Path path) throws ImplerException
      Creates .java file that contains the implementation of the interface passed as a parameter clazz on the path passed as parameter path. As a result, the java code of the class with the Impl suffix is generated, implementing the specified interface. The generated class compiles without errors. The generated class is public and not abstract. Methods of the generated class ignore their arguments and return default values.
      Specified by:
      implement in interface Impler
      Parameters:
      clazz - interface that should be implemented.
      path - path where .java file should be located.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if some errors occurred during the implementation.

    • printReturnType

      private void printReturnType​(BufferedWriter codePrinter, Class<?> returnType) throws IOException
      Prints default return value. Prints default return value of method that was the parameter method of printMethod(BufferedWriter, Method) method. If type of return value is not a primitive then method will print "null" in output file as return value. Else if type of return value is not a void and is not a boolean then method will print "0" in output file as return value. Else if type of return value is boolean then method will print "false" in output file as return value. Otherwise,(in case when type of return value is void) method won't print any return value.
      Parameters:
      codePrinter - BufferedWriter to write in output file.
      returnType - type of return value.
      Throws:
      IOException - if some errors occurred during writing in output file.
